{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, the causal mechanisms underpinning our results remain unformalized.",
    "While our study demonstrates the effectiveness of AI-facilitated dialogues in changing conspiracy beliefs, the specific cognitive or psychological processes through which this change occurs are unusually difficult to confirmeach conversation was unique and contained an admixture of rational argumentation and social cues.",
    "Both qualitative examination of the conversations and a structured, NLP-based analysis of the persuasive strategies used by the AI (see SM Section 6) suggest that fact-based argumentation was the focal point of each interaction; future research should examine this in greater detail.",
    "It has become almost a truism that people \"down the rabbit hole\" of conspiracy belief are almost impossible to reach.",
    "In contrast to this pessimistic view, we have shown that a relatively brief conversation with a generative AI model can produce a large and lasting decrease in conspiracy beliefs, even among people whose beliefs are deeply entrenched."
  ]
}